  e.well_typed' ε := by
  induction e with
  | base =>
    intro hwf hwt
    dsimp [well_typed'] at *
    simp [hwf, hwt]
    <;> tauto
  | product e1 e2 he1 he2 =>
    intro hwf hwt
    simp [hwf, hwt, well_typed', well_formed] at *
    <;> tauto
```

This looks like a reasonable approach. The use of `<;> tauto` applies `tauto` to all goals produced by `simp`. This should complete the proof.
</think>
